01:00.960 --> 01:04.296
[music playing
on television]

01:09.302 --> 01:12.004
- Uh, maybe it's time
to buy a new recliner.

01:12.006 --> 01:16.975
- Buy a new recliner?
Easy for you to say,
moneybags bunny.

01:16.977 --> 01:19.111
But unlike you,
I wasn't born

01:19.113 --> 01:21.947
With a silver carrot
in my mouth.

01:21.949 --> 01:22.815
- Well, then get it fixed.

01:22.817 --> 01:26.385
- Why? If it ain't broke,
don't fix it.

01:27.520 --> 01:28.954
Ooh!

01:28.956 --> 01:31.423
[groans]

01:31.425 --> 01:32.458
- It is broke.

01:32.460 --> 01:34.927
- It's an expression, bugs.

01:34.929 --> 01:36.095
Lord, you're ignorant.

01:36.097 --> 01:39.965
My point is, I'm perfectly
content with it like this.

01:39.967 --> 01:40.766
- Well, I'm not.

01:40.768 --> 01:42.468
It takes up half the room
this way.

01:42.470 --> 01:44.636
And I'm not watching tv
upside down.

01:44.638 --> 01:46.205
- [scoffs]
you're so prickly.

01:46.207 --> 01:48.207
Everything has to be
just so with you.

01:48.209 --> 01:50.542
It's like you can't adapt.

01:50.544 --> 01:51.944
Ohh! My eyes!

01:51.946 --> 01:55.948
The sudden change in lighting.
I can't adapt to it.

01:55.950 --> 01:57.549
[sobbing]

01:57.851 --> 02:02.121
Why is it so hard
for you to admit that
you lost, porky?

02:02.123 --> 02:03.856
- [stammering]
I didn't lose.

02:03.858 --> 02:06.325
In golf,
the lowest score wins.

02:06.327 --> 02:07.993
- That doesn't make
any sense.

02:07.995 --> 02:09.828
Everyone knows
that in sports,

02:09.830 --> 02:11.530
The highest score wins.

02:11.532 --> 02:16.001
You got a 75.
I got a 308.

02:16.003 --> 02:17.369
I dominated you.

02:17.371 --> 02:20.772
[scoffs]
he put the tv back.

02:20.774 --> 02:22.774
[gasps]

02:25.044 --> 02:28.113
What in the name of
randall mcclintock is this?

02:28.115 --> 02:30.782
- Ooh, a new recliner.

02:30.784 --> 02:31.850
- What do you think?

02:31.852 --> 02:33.785
- Are you responsible
for this?

02:33.787 --> 02:35.187
- Well, your old one
was broken.

02:35.189 --> 02:38.123
This one's brand new.
It's leather.

02:38.125 --> 02:41.193
- No, absolutely not.
Take it back.

02:41.195 --> 02:41.827
- Why?

02:41.829 --> 02:42.961
I think it's nice.

02:42.963 --> 02:44.663
- Oh, now I definitely
don't want it.

02:44.665 --> 02:47.166
Porky has the worst taste
of anyone I know.

02:47.168 --> 02:49.201
- You think I have
bad taste?

02:49.203 --> 02:50.202
- Look in the mirror, man.

02:50.204 --> 02:52.271
What's with those shoes?
They're crazy.

02:52.273 --> 02:54.206
They have little spikes
on the bottom.

02:54.208 --> 02:55.040
Who does that?

02:55.042 --> 02:56.108
- They're golf shoes.

02:56.110 --> 02:57.709
- Well, what's with
the one glove?

02:57.711 --> 02:59.778
Who do you think you are,
michael jackson?

02:59.780 --> 03:03.782
I met michael jackson,
and you are no michael jackson.

03:04.017 --> 03:05.817
- It's a golf glove.

03:05.819 --> 03:07.519
- When did you meet
michael jackson?

03:07.521 --> 03:09.254
- I met him at
the denver airport.

03:09.256 --> 03:10.289
But that's not the point.

03:10.291 --> 03:12.457
The point is,
I want my old recliner back.

03:12.459 --> 03:15.127
- It's too late.
I donated it to
a thrift store.

03:15.129 --> 03:20.632
- Porky, I'm gonna need
a moment alone with my roommate.

03:20.634 --> 03:24.503
Not my friend,
my roommate.

03:24.505 --> 03:26.271
- Oh, uh, ok.

03:26.273 --> 03:27.172
[crash]

03:27.174 --> 03:28.840
- That was a garbage move.

03:28.842 --> 03:31.877
- Getting you a brand new
recliner was a garbage move?

03:31.879 --> 03:35.214
- That recliner meant
everything to me.

03:35.281 --> 03:36.748
- Why?
- Why?

03:36.750 --> 03:38.850
It was my sole possession.

03:38.852 --> 03:39.751
- What are you talking about?

03:39.753 --> 03:41.620
You got a bedroom
full of stuff.

03:41.622 --> 03:43.422
- Yes, but all of that
is either rented,

03:43.424 --> 03:46.792
Found in a dumpster,
or I'm borrowing it from porky.

03:46.794 --> 03:49.962
That recliner I bought
with my own money.

03:49.964 --> 03:52.798
It was the summer
after graduation.

03:52.800 --> 03:55.934
I was working at
that-a-burger.

03:55.936 --> 03:56.868
It was miserable.

03:56.870 --> 03:59.838
6 days a week,
10 hours a day,

03:59.840 --> 04:02.274
Standing over
those grease traps,

04:02.276 --> 04:04.543
Slinging 80% beef patties.

04:04.545 --> 04:08.213
I used to fantasize
about sitting down

04:08.448 --> 04:10.015
With my feet up,

04:10.017 --> 04:12.517
Just relaxing.

04:12.519 --> 04:18.690
Then one day on my walk
home from yet another
nightmare shift,

04:18.692 --> 04:23.996
I looked up and there it was
in the storefront window.

04:23.998 --> 04:26.431
I knew if I could just
sit in it once,

04:26.433 --> 04:29.701
I would sit in it
for the rest of my life.

04:29.703 --> 04:33.105
But they said
I had to buy it.

04:34.107 --> 04:37.442
It took me all summer
to make enough money,

04:37.444 --> 04:40.012
But once I did,
I quit that job,

04:40.014 --> 04:45.517
Bought that recliner,
and I've been sitting in it
ever since.

04:45.519 --> 04:47.819
Until today.

04:47.821 --> 04:50.522
- Wow. I had no idea.

04:50.524 --> 04:53.091
I feel terrible.

04:53.093 --> 04:54.092
Come on.

04:54.094 --> 04:55.327
- Where are we going?

04:55.329 --> 04:59.131
- To get your recliner back.

05:01.034 --> 05:04.836
- Uh, guys?

05:04.838 --> 05:06.838
Hello?

05:07.273 --> 05:11.276
- I can't believe someone
already bought my recliner.

05:11.278 --> 05:14.212
- Neither can I.

05:15.715 --> 05:18.283
- Now what am I gonna do?

05:18.285 --> 05:19.618
Where am I gonna sit?

05:19.620 --> 05:21.853
- In the new recliner
I got you.

05:21.855 --> 05:22.954
It's very comfortable.

05:22.956 --> 05:25.757
Give it a try.
Maybe you'll like it.

05:25.759 --> 05:27.826
Think of it as
a new beginning,

05:27.828 --> 05:28.760
A fresh start.

05:28.762 --> 05:31.029
When one door closes,
another one opens.

05:31.031 --> 05:32.764
That's what makes life
interesting.

05:32.766 --> 05:35.967
You never know what's
gonna happen next.

05:36.636 --> 05:37.703
[crunch]
- ooh!

05:37.705 --> 05:41.807
- Bet you didn't know
that was gonna happen.

05:42.608 --> 05:44.109
- Are you ok?

05:44.111 --> 05:45.944
- You hit me.

05:45.946 --> 05:47.946
Buges buney?

05:47.948 --> 05:48.814
- Cecil?

05:48.816 --> 05:50.515
Here, let me help you up.

05:50.517 --> 05:52.918
I'm so sorry.
Are you hurt?

05:52.920 --> 05:54.353
- No, I think I'm ok.

05:54.355 --> 05:58.156
Just a little startled,
maybe.

05:58.158 --> 06:00.092
- Uh-oh.
- What?

06:00.094 --> 06:02.928
- Did you always have
a crack in your shell?

06:02.930 --> 06:05.497
- Oh, no,
my shell is cracked.

06:05.499 --> 06:07.966
- Don't worry,
I'll take care of it.
I have insurance.

06:07.968 --> 06:11.670
- Oh, no, I don't want you
to have to go through
all that trouble.

06:11.672 --> 06:13.772
Let's handle this
like gentlemen.

06:13.774 --> 06:15.507
I have a shell guy
I go to.

06:15.509 --> 06:17.376
He's very reasonable.

06:17.378 --> 06:18.677
- Well, whatever the cost.

06:18.679 --> 06:21.346
Whatever it is,
I'll be happy to pay for it.

06:21.414 --> 06:22.581
Here's my number.

06:22.583 --> 06:24.950
- I'll be in touch.

06:24.952 --> 06:26.151
Ohh.

06:26.153 --> 06:27.419
Uhh.

06:27.421 --> 06:29.187
Uhh. Uhh.

06:29.189 --> 06:30.255
[starts engine]

06:30.257 --> 06:31.156
- What are you doing?

06:31.158 --> 06:33.992
- I think you've done
enough damage for one day.

06:33.994 --> 06:39.331
Being behind the wheel
of a car is a tremendous
responsibility, bugs.

06:39.333 --> 06:42.200
It requires concentration
and focus.

06:42.202 --> 06:45.871
That's how you avoid
accidents.

06:54.580 --> 06:56.248
- So, what do you think?

06:56.250 --> 06:57.916
- What kind of leather
is this?

06:57.918 --> 06:59.851
- I don't know. Leather.

06:59.853 --> 07:02.421
- Is it corinthian
or cordovan?

07:02.423 --> 07:04.022
Or is it even leather at all?

07:04.024 --> 07:06.925
I mean, it feels like
naugahyde.

07:06.927 --> 07:07.759
- It's leather.

07:07.761 --> 07:10.595
- It makes a weird sound
when I move like this.

07:10.597 --> 07:12.597
- Well, then stop
moving like that.

07:12.599 --> 07:13.665
- I don't think I like it.

07:13.667 --> 07:15.801
- Daffy, you're the only
person in the world

07:15.803 --> 07:17.135
That wouldn't like
this recliner.

07:17.137 --> 07:20.939
- Ugh. Where did you get
this hideous recliner?

07:20.941 --> 07:23.341
- See? Told you.
It's going back.

07:23.343 --> 07:25.677
- What?
It's just one opinion.

07:25.778 --> 07:28.947
- Uh, one professional
opinion.

07:28.949 --> 07:30.015
- You're not a professional.

07:30.017 --> 07:32.918
- Uh, no, but I watch
"design divas" every week,

07:32.920 --> 07:35.287
So I think I know
what I'm talking about.

07:35.289 --> 07:36.922
- What is "design divas"?

07:36.924 --> 07:38.590
- It's the design show
where diva decorators

07:38.592 --> 07:42.294
Change other divas' lives
one piece of furniture
at a time.

07:42.296 --> 07:44.963
- Hello! We have
a season pass to it.

07:44.965 --> 07:46.798
How have you never seen it?

07:46.800 --> 07:49.868
Ugh. Always with
the reading, this guy.

07:49.870 --> 07:51.169
- What happened to
your old recliner?

07:51.171 --> 07:54.639
- Brainiac over there thought
he was doing me a favor

07:54.641 --> 07:55.507
By throwing it away

07:55.509 --> 07:59.511
And giving me this--
this naugahyde nightmare.

07:59.513 --> 08:01.980
- It's beyond horrible.

08:04.116 --> 08:06.952
- It's nice.

08:06.954 --> 08:09.421
- Bugs, you're good
in a lot of areas,

08:09.423 --> 08:10.922
But home decor is
not one of them.

08:10.924 --> 08:13.925
You just don't see things
the way we do.

08:13.927 --> 08:15.360
[telephone rings]

08:15.362 --> 08:17.095
- That's an understatement.

08:17.097 --> 08:19.331
[ring]

08:19.333 --> 08:20.699
[ring]

08:20.701 --> 08:21.500
Hello?

08:21.502 --> 08:22.834
- Buges, it's cecil.

08:22.836 --> 08:24.669
- Oh, hi.
How are you?

08:24.671 --> 08:26.304
- The turtle.
- Yeah, right.

08:26.306 --> 08:28.340
- The one you hit
with your car this morning.

08:28.342 --> 08:30.375
- No, yeah, I know
exactly who this is.

08:30.377 --> 08:34.712
- Ok, well, I just dropped
my shell off with my shell guy

08:34.715 --> 08:38.750
And the crack is worse
than we thought.

08:38.751 --> 08:40.818
- Oh, no.
What does that mean?

08:40.821 --> 08:44.022
- It means he's
gonna need $2,000.

08:44.024 --> 08:45.957
- $2,000 to fix your shell?

08:45.959 --> 08:50.362
- Oh, no, the 2,000 is
just to go in and see
what the problem is.

08:50.364 --> 08:53.798
He has to determine
if it's a surface crack

08:53.800 --> 08:55.767
Or a sub-stratum crack.

08:55.769 --> 08:57.369
If it's a sub-stratum crack,

08:57.371 --> 09:00.805
That could end up costing
as much as 35.

09:00.807 --> 09:02.474
- 3,500?

09:02.476 --> 09:03.942
- 35,000.

09:03.944 --> 09:04.776
- [gulps]

09:04.778 --> 09:09.414
- But fingers crossed
it's a surface crack.

09:09.515 --> 09:11.917
So you want to drop
that check off?

09:11.919 --> 09:15.754
I'd come by and get it,
but I probably shouldn't
leave the house.

09:15.756 --> 09:18.757
You know, turtle
without a shell.

09:18.759 --> 09:19.958
Highly vulnerable.

09:19.960 --> 09:23.161
- Oh, of course.
What's your address?

09:23.163 --> 09:24.663
- 4123--

09:24.665 --> 09:25.931
- Can I have your credit card?

09:25.933 --> 09:26.665
- My credit card?

09:26.667 --> 09:28.600
- Oh, actually,
I'd prefer a check.

09:28.602 --> 09:31.202
- No, I'm sorry,
I wasn't talking to you.

09:31.204 --> 09:32.771
Why do you need
my credit card?

09:32.773 --> 09:34.639
- We're exchanging
the recliner.

09:34.641 --> 09:35.473
- Hello?

09:35.475 --> 09:36.508
- Oh, uh, sorry.

09:36.510 --> 09:37.375
Can you say that again?

09:37.377 --> 09:39.711
- We are exchanging
the recliner.

09:39.779 --> 09:41.947
- Not you.
No, I'm sorry,

09:41.949 --> 09:43.815
I wasn't talking to you.

09:43.817 --> 09:44.916
Here.

09:44.918 --> 09:47.953
Sorry.
One more time, cecil.

09:47.955 --> 09:50.455
- 4123 helms way.

09:50.457 --> 09:52.624
- Sorry.
Where'd you buy it?

09:52.626 --> 09:54.459
- Home warehouse.

09:54.461 --> 09:56.761
- No. Helms way.

09:56.763 --> 09:59.164
Why would I live
at home warehouse?

09:59.166 --> 10:00.031
- It's not important.

10:00.033 --> 10:02.133
I'll stop by
with the check.

10:02.135 --> 10:02.934
[beep]

10:02.936 --> 10:04.869
- Can you help us carry
the recliner to the car?

10:04.871 --> 10:07.606
It's real heavy.

10:08.774 --> 10:12.177
- Great day of the morning.
This place is huge.

10:12.179 --> 10:13.745
We've been walking around
for an hour

10:13.747 --> 10:15.914
And just got out of
the kitchen section.

10:15.916 --> 10:16.982
Where are we now?

10:16.984 --> 10:17.983
- Hmm. I don't know.

10:17.985 --> 10:20.018
It's either textiles
and rugs

10:20.020 --> 10:23.121
Or storage solutions.

10:26.225 --> 10:28.426
- A scarf basket?

10:28.428 --> 10:30.261
Who needs a scarf basket?

10:30.263 --> 10:31.830
- Ooh! Look over here!

10:31.832 --> 10:32.831
- You found the recliners?

10:32.833 --> 10:35.300
- No, it's a complete
closet organizing system.

10:35.302 --> 10:38.503
See, everything is
divided into little baskets.

10:38.505 --> 10:40.138
- Baskets. Genius.

10:40.140 --> 10:41.773
- All of your t-shirts
go in here,

10:41.775 --> 10:42.974
Socks and underwear here.

10:42.976 --> 10:43.975
This is for your sweaters.

10:44.076 --> 10:45.977
- What about my scarves?

10:45.979 --> 10:47.078
- Look, scarf baskets.

10:47.080 --> 10:52.350
- Ohh, my mornings would
go so much quicker if
my closet looked like this.

10:52.352 --> 10:53.785
- Hmph. Tell me about it.

10:53.787 --> 10:56.855
- You know,
about 7 years ago,
I quit wearing clothes

10:56.857 --> 10:59.591
Because my closet
was so disorganized.

10:59.593 --> 11:00.792
I just gave up.

11:00.794 --> 11:03.528
- Oh. Em. Gee.

11:03.530 --> 11:04.696
- You found the recliners?

11:04.698 --> 11:07.766
- More like patio furniture
and outdoor dining!

11:07.768 --> 11:09.868
- Ooh! Wait for me!

11:15.441 --> 11:18.510
- Oh, mr. Buney.
Forgive my appearance.

11:18.911 --> 11:21.946
Let me go and get a robe.

11:21.948 --> 11:25.283
- I just wanted
to give you your check.

11:25.285 --> 11:27.786
- Oh, that's so nice of you.

11:27.788 --> 11:29.354
$2,000. Yep.

11:29.356 --> 11:31.623
This should get
the ball rolling.

11:31.625 --> 11:32.824
- How are you feeling?

11:32.826 --> 11:35.627
- Oh, you know,
not good.

11:35.629 --> 11:39.831
- I'm really sorry.
Is there anything else
I can do for you?

11:39.833 --> 11:43.101
- Well, I suppose
I could use some groceries.

11:43.103 --> 11:43.868
- Oh.

11:43.870 --> 11:45.704
- I mean, I'd go
and get them myself,

11:45.706 --> 11:48.206
But a turtle
without a shell...

11:48.208 --> 11:50.542
- Right. Highly vulnerable.

11:50.544 --> 11:52.143
- Here's a list.

11:52.145 --> 11:54.779
- You, uh, had that
ready to go, huh?

11:54.781 --> 11:57.449
- I'd really appreciate it.

11:57.451 --> 12:01.152
- Ok. I'll be right back.

12:01.154 --> 12:02.954
- [chuckles]

12:02.956 --> 12:05.790
[cackles]

12:08.728 --> 12:10.962
- Were you just laughing?

12:10.964 --> 12:11.863
- What? No.

12:11.865 --> 12:15.433
- It sounded like
the evil laugh of
a cartoon villain.

12:15.435 --> 12:17.502
- Oh, don't be silly.

12:17.504 --> 12:21.806
I mean, do I look
like a cartoon villain?

12:22.842 --> 12:26.478
- Who are you looking at?

12:37.790 --> 12:39.457
- Uh-huh. Uh-huh.

12:39.459 --> 12:42.093
I'm on with my shell guy.

12:44.063 --> 12:47.832
- So you're saying
it can't be repaired?

12:47.834 --> 12:50.769
You're gonna have to make
a brand new custom shell?

12:50.771 --> 12:55.140
I don't even want to ask
how much that's gonna cost.

12:55.142 --> 12:57.142
Of course, I'll hold.

12:57.144 --> 12:58.510
He's pricing it out for me.

12:58.512 --> 13:01.746
Looks like it's gonna be
a little more than we hoped.

13:01.748 --> 13:03.782
- Hmm. What a shocker.

13:03.784 --> 13:07.619
Where would you like me
to put all this caviar I bought?

13:07.621 --> 13:08.686
- Fridge is fine.

13:08.688 --> 13:12.690
Oh, good, you remembered
the bubbly.

13:12.692 --> 13:13.825
Oh, yes, hi.

13:13.827 --> 13:16.094
Did you come up
with a figure?

13:16.096 --> 13:17.796
Oh, boy.
Oh, brother.

13:17.798 --> 13:19.464
Oh, brother.
Oh, boy.

13:19.466 --> 13:23.368
He says you're looking
at $53,000.

13:23.370 --> 13:24.435
- Let me talk to him.

13:24.437 --> 13:27.105
- Oh, uh, uh, you can't.

13:27.107 --> 13:27.972
- Why not?

13:27.974 --> 13:29.974
- Because he, um,
doesn't speak english.

13:29.976 --> 13:31.442
- You were just talking
to him in english.

13:31.444 --> 13:35.246
- Oh, well, he can understand
it, he just can't speak it.

13:35.248 --> 13:36.648
- Give me that phone.

13:36.650 --> 13:38.650
